==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manila hemp
<hw>Manila hemp</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fibrous material
obtained from the abaca plant (<spn>Musa textilis</spn>), a plant allied
to the banana, growing in the Philippine and other East India islands;
-- called also by the native name <altname>abaca</altname>. From it
matting, canvas, ropes, and cables are made.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Manilla hemp, abaca.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A Philippine plant (<spn>Musa textilis</spn>) having
leafstalks that yield Manila hemp used for rope and paper etc.; called
also the <altname>abaca</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manila maguey</ent>⟦br⟧
